demonstrate that it produces more accurate estimates of the whole
population than standard procedures based on weighting by inverse
detection efficiency. We apply the method to an existing catalog of
small planet candidates around G dwarf stars. We confirm a previous
result that the radius distribution changes slope near Earth's radius.
We find that the rate density of Earth analogs is about 0.02 (per star
per natural logarithmic bin in period and radius) with large
uncertainty. This number is much smaller than previous estimates made
with the same data but stronger assumptions.},
